frus:attachment.p:
—Its activities, particularly the most expensive activities of intelligence
                        collection and processing, must be managed in an efficient or generally cost
                        effective manner;

list.item:
• depending on circumstances, may or may not be illegal (and even
                            where illegal, may be more important to contain and counter than to
                            prosecute);

• affect our international relationships, and infringe upon the
                            responsibilities (often conflicting) of a number of departments and
                            agencies;

—formulation and review of foreign counterintelligence policy and
                            objectives, oversight of their implementation and examination of their
                            effectiveness;
